
╔═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╗
║  MISSION: COOLING SYSTEM BATCH REPAIR                                     ║
║  SKILL: xargs (batch operations)                                          ║
╚═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╝

OBJECTIVE:
Multiple cooling sensor files need to be processed. Instead of handling
them one by one, use xargs to perform batch operations efficiently.

━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

TASK: Extract Critical Readings
───────────────────────────────
The directory contains multiple sensor log files (sensor_*.log).
Each file contains temperature readings with some marked as "CRITICAL".

Your task:
1. Find all CRITICAL readings across ALL sensor files
2. Count the total number of CRITICAL readings
3. The answer is the total count

Use xargs to efficiently search all files at once.

When you have the count, run:
    ./verify <count>

━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

USEFUL COMMANDS:
    ls sensor_*.log                          List sensor files
    ls sensor_*.log | xargs grep "CRITICAL"  Search all files
    ls sensor_*.log | xargs grep -c "CRIT"   Count per file

    find . -name "sensor_*.log" | xargs grep "CRITICAL"
    find . -name "*.log" -exec grep "CRITICAL" {} \;

TO COUNT TOTAL:
    ls *.log | xargs grep "CRITICAL" | wc -l
    grep -r "CRITICAL" *.log | wc -l

━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

